cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a heterogeneous network with mobile edge computing, which involves wireless communication and network architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm for computation offloading and resource allocation, which falls under the category of distributed computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the system-wide computation overhead, which involves control and optimization of the system. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of joint optimization of individual computation decisions, transmit power of the users, and computation resource at the servers, which involves information theory and communication. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses matching games for user association and subchannel assignment, which falls under the category of game theory.
